				<h3 class='content_title'>Toronto Transit Speeds</h3>

			<p>A data exploration project visualizing the speed of every surface route of 
				the TTC. All the TTC buses and streetcars traced for 6 hours the morning of 
				January 6th, 2012.  Average speed is indicated by colour, red being the slowest, 
				followed by orange, yellow, green and blue.
			</p>	
							
			<p>Check out the feature in <a href="http://torontoist.com/2012/01/colour-coding-your-commute/">Torontoist</a>, 
				as well as some mentions in the
				<a href="http://www.thestar.com/news/transportation/article/1121806--ttc-routes-during-rush-hour-watch-them-all-at-once">Toronto Star</a> and
				<a href="http://www.globaltoronto.com/video/a+birdseye+view+of+the+ttc/video.html?v=2190485386#segments/video">Global News</a>.
			</p>
									
			<p>Thanks to Open Data Toronto.  Build using Processing, QGIS, and some Photoshop for touchups.</p>
			
